The paper deals with discrete schemes for Gaussian curvature, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The convergence property of the schemes is also discussed, which involves numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also presents a new discrete scheme, which falls under the category of graphics (cs.GR) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the comparison of asymptotic errors involves statistical inference (cs.SI).
